	<text>
		<body>
			<p>From Minister <persName ref="#ehri_dr_akira_yamaji">Yamaji Akira</persName> (<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/727011/sofia.html"
					>Sofia</placeName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/732800/republic-of-bulgaria.html">Bulgaria</placeName>) </p>
			<p>To: Foreign Minister <persName ref="#ehri_dr_mamoru_shigemitsu">Shigemitsu Mamoru</persName> (<placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/1850147/tokyo.html">Tokyo</placeName>)</p>
			<p><q>Concerning the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-351" type="subject">Jewish Question</term></q></p>
			<p>Currently there are about 50,000 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864?dlid=eng" type="subject">Jews</term>
				in this country, of which about 26,000 live in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/727011/sofia.html">Sofia</placeName>. Although
				they do not appear to have any influence in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-708?dlid=eng"
					type="subject">cultural sphere</term>, in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-924" type="subject"
					>business</term> (especially commerce) they are extremely influential. As a result, there is increasingly the view that something
				must be done about this. In response to this, In the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-365" type="subject"
					> “Law for the Protection of the nation,”</term> promulgated in <date when="1941-01">January 1941</date>, the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">Government</term> established several articles
				concerning the Jewish population. However, the actual effect was rather limited. As a result, last fall the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">government</term> received full authority to deal with
				the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term>. </p>
			<p>Consequently, they established a new bureau and required <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864"
					type="subject">Jews</term> to wear <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-338" type="subject">yellow
					tags</term>, placed <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-658" type="subject">limitation</term> on their
				residence as well as on their activities besides business, and their control of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-945" type="subject">property</term> 2.6 billion leva etc. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">government</term> pursued a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-594" type="subject">policy</term> similar to that of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Germany</placeName>. However, such <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-594" type="subject">policies</term> were not very popular. In January this
				year the vice speaker of the Parliament and about forty members of the Parliament criticized the government measures, leading to the
				resignation of the vice speaker. (There is rumor that the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864"
					type="subject">Jews</term> spent a lot of money for this). </p>
			<p>Recently many <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> are accused of being
				involved in terror, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-253" type="subject">sabotage</term>, spying and
				other forms of political agitation, and engaging in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1051" type="subject"
					>black market</term> that should be called the cancer of Bulgarian <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-918" type="subject">economy</term>. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">government</term> came to force <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> living in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/727011/sofia.html">Sofia</placeName> to relocate to local areas because it was not very successful to
				leave the matter to their own will (only 2,600 had <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject"
					>moved out</term> so far)</p>
			<p> That is to say, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">government</term> will notify
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> about the destination for their
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1173" type="subject">relocation</term> within two to three weeks.
				After receiving the notice the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> must
				leave the city within three days. Concerning this new measure the head of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-774" type="subject">Orthodox Church</term>
				<persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000014">Stefan</persName> and others lodged <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-984" type="subject">protest</term> against and it was not very popular in
				general. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">Government</term>, however, considers
				that the city’s <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-917" type="subject">political and economic</term>
				condition will improve after the expulsion of all of its <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864"
					type="subject">Jews</term>. 12,000 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term>
				who live in the new territories of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/718075/north-macedonia.html">Macedonia</placeName> and
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/738770/thrace.html">Thrace</placeName> have been <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">deported</term> to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName>. (Now the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> who live in these new territories are
				mainly those with foreign <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1147" type="subject">citizenship</term> and
				number no more than 6,700.) Although there was a plan to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518"
					type="subject">deport</term> the 10,000 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject"
					>Jews</term> who live in the old territories, as a result of the new measure this plan was put on hold. </p>
			<p>Through the intermediary of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2658434/switzerland.html">Switzerland</placeName>, the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/732800/republic-of-bulgaria.html">Bulgarian</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">Government</term> has reached an agreement with
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2635167/united-kingdom-of-great-britain-and-northern-ireland.html">Britain</placeName> to
				send 5,000 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/6254930/palestine.html">Palestine</placeName>. However, they became entangled in the detailed
				articles and the agreement had not been implemented. </p>
